The Emir of Kano, Aminu Ado Bayero, has paid a courtesy visit to Bola Tinubu, National Leader of the All Progressives Congress, APC. Tinubu hosted Bayero during a courtesy call at his Bourdillon residence in Ikoyi, Lagos State over the weekend. The meeting was disclosed via Tinubu’s official Twitter handle. <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-858098" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/tinubu-emir-of-kano2-scaled.jpg" alt="" width="2560" height="1711" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/tinubu-emir-of-kano2-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/tinubu-emir-of-kano2-300x201.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/tinubu-emir-of-kano2-1024x685.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/tinubu-emir-of-kano2-1536x1027.jpg 1536w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/tinubu-emir-of-kano2-2048x1369.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px"> At the time of filing this report, the agenda of the meeting was unknown. This is coming at a time when Tinubu had harped on the unity of Nigeria. He had Tinubu made the remark during the wedding Fatiha of Sheikh Muhammad Uthman’s daughter in Kano. Speaking during the event, Tinubu had commended Bin Uthman for his efforts as a committed Islamic scholar and advocate of the unity, progress, peace and development of the country.